Pinus tenuifolia

    Authority   Benth.
      Family    Pinopsida:Pinaceae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 8661

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION
   An evergreen tree.
   GROWING PERIOD
   Perennial. The tree can withstand 4-6 months of drought.
   COMMON NAMES
   Cantaj, Ocote.
   FURTHER INF
   Cantaj occurs in southern Mexico in the state of Chiapas at elevations
   between 800-1900 m. It is usually found on hills and slopes, but can
   also occur on flat land.

   Sources
   SOURCES
   Serrano C 1978 pp 15-16 [RAIN, TEMP, TEXT, FER, PH, DRA, DEP]

